Any person possessing a moderate acquaintance with the history of ancient philosophy and the contests of the various schools knows that the fighting was not always done with fair weaponS, but that misrepresentation and unjust deductions from the adversaries' propositions were not uncommon. We must recognize the reproach as well founded that the Epicurean theology undermined and destroyed all religion j worthy of the name ; and when Epicurus notwithstanding this talked of pious reverence for the gods because of their essential excellence. we may at least doubt whether he was really in earnest.
